This paper discusses the formalization of fairness in machine learning algorithms for prediction, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the social implications of fairness formalizations, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the potential for discrimination in machine learning algorithms, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
